{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: source clients -> aggregator/orchestrator -> summary input payload. A pure unit test of one function can miss wiring/mapping mistakes between modules. Rejected System: behavior text only requires verifying composed payload includes three source datasets; no concrete requirement for real network/OS/subprocess. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: this behavior validates pre-generation input completeness, not model output quality or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Wire the real data-collection/orchestration modules with three deterministic test adapters (metrics, issue tracker, deployment log) and a spy/fake summary generator. Assert the exact payload handed to summary generation contains non-empty sections from all three adapters with correct source attribution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at interaction boundary between source-fetch error handling and report assembly. Need multiple modules wired to verify partial-failure propagation and graceful degradation. Rejected System: unavailability can be reproduced with in-process adapter errors/timeouts; behavior does not require real network semantics. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: requirement is fallback control flow, not model judgment quality or multi-agent chain.","test_description":"Run orchestrator with two healthy source adapters and one adapter that raises a fetch error. Assert execution completes, final report includes a `data unavailable` marker only for the failing section, and email/send stage still receives a report object instead of pipeline abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on generation quality of the summary step (factual representation of key values), which is model-output dependent and potentially non-deterministic. A stubbed generator would always pass and hide hallucination/omission failures. Rejected Workflow: behavior text refers to one summary-generation step, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Use a fixed, representative dataset with known key values; call the real summary-generation model/config repeatedly and score outputs with factual checks (required values present, no value inversion, no fabricated metrics). Pass criterion is a stability/accuracy threshold across runs rather than a single deterministic string match.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external I/O (HTTP/API fetches and email transport/inbox delivery). In-process mocks can hide SMTP/auth/routing/connectivity and message-format issues that only appear end-to-end. Rejected Agentic: behavior checks delivery to inbox, not semantic quality of model output; higher agentic level is not required for this specific assertion. Rejected Workflow: no multi-agent decision chain requirement in behavior text.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled script in an environment with reachable test instances of the three sources and a real test mailbox. Verify one run produces an email in the configured inbox with expected subject/body sections and source-derived content present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior spans real infrastructure boundaries: email transport failure plus filesystem persistence across runs/schedule cycles. Mocks often miss real file-permission/path durability and retry-after-restart behavior. Rejected Integration: wording explicitly requires next scheduled run retry and local file fallback, which is cross-run infra behavior. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: correctness is retry/fallback mechanics, not model decision quality.","test_description":"Run 1: make email service unreachable, execute scheduler/script, assert report is persisted to configured local fallback path. Run 2 (next scheduled invocation): restore email service, execute again, assert persisted report is retried/sent and fallback artifact/state is cleared or marked delivered per design.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
